  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: Unread counter shows number of unread messages in the chat (1:1 or public). Counter disappears, so it looks like all messages are read after app is relaunched even if user didn't open the chat.\r\n\r\nIt worked ok in previous 0.9.26 release\r\n\r\nNow: \r\nBefore relaunch:\r\n\r\n![screenshot_20180904-115741](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/45024700-e7992d00-b039-11e8-8690-976b95014b2d.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nAfter relaunch (chats were not opened)\r\n![screenshot_20180904-115822](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/45024707-ec5de100-b039-11e8-99c2-e5959c4fc0f3.png)\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nUnread counter shows number of unread messages or 9+ if there are > 9 messages even if app is relaunched.  It should disappear only after user opened the chat and read (seen) all messages\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nUnread counter disappears after app is relaunched \r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status and log in\r\n- When on Home tab get 10 messages in 1:1 and in public chat - check there is unread counter shown next to each chat with unread messages. Do not open chats\r\n- Close app\r\n- Launch app and log in\r\n- Check if there is unread counter shown next to the chats\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: release 0.9.27  build https://jenkins.status.im/job/status-react/job/release/job/release%252F0.9.27/8/\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote><img src=\"/static/c32cacaf/favicon.ico\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><strong><a href=\"https://jenkins.status.im/job/status-react/job/release/job/release%252F0.9.27/8/\">status-react » release » release/0.9.27 #8 [Jenkins]</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
